{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Working with PMTiles"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pmtiles:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"asset:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load an asset or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"file:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a local PMTiles file."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"PMTiles sources currently do not support caching or offline pack downloads.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":""},{"text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles"},{"text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile server.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"pmtiles-demo.png","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind